cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.DM, cs.AL, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with two fundamental problems in data streaming research: detecting frequent items and detecting large neighborhoods in graph streams. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the use of approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Cryptography). The problem of detecting frequent items with timestamps is related to data mining, which is covered under cs.DM (Database and Information Retrieval). The paper also involves communication complexity, which is covered under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the problem of detecting large neighborhoods in graph streams is related to social network analysis, which is covered under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
